create-react-app

command to create a react app on terminal:
    npx create-react-app appname

You need:
- browser console 
- text editor 
- application running on browser 

console.log('message')
- prints message onto the browser console 
message can have dynamic js in it using { }
e.g. "this is the message and the variable is {a}"

React components are actually written in JSX 
- with JSX you can easily make dymanic content by embedding javsacript in the curly brackets 

Root component called App is at the top of the component tree of the application 

passing data to components using props
- adding a parameter to the component function 
- as an argument, the parameter receives an object which has fields corresponding to all the props the user of the component defines 

- Component names must be capitalised 
